    "for_type": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000",
    "displayName": "Sortable List",
    "capabilities": [
      "read",
      "write"
    ],
    "description": "Sortable lists provide drag-to-reorder functionality for item attachments displayed in a linear list (as opposed to the spatial canvas layout).\n\n## Concept\n\nWhile the [spatial windowing system](item://ef793c27-2d4b-4c99-b05a-2769db5bc5a9) arranges children on a 2D canvas, some contexts benefit from an ordered list:\n\n- Todo lists where order represents priority\n- Document outlines where order represents sequence\n- Playlists, reading lists, step-by-step instructions\n\nSortable lists render attachments in array order with drag handles for reordering.\n\n## Implementation\n\nThe reorder operation modifies the parent item's `attachments` array:\n\n1. User drags an item to a new position\n2. The attachment is removed from its current index\n3. Inserted at the target index\n4. Parent item saved with `api.update()` to reflect new order\n\nThe `attachments` array is ordered — array position determines display order.\n\n## Drag Interaction\n\n- Drag handle (grip icon) on each list item\n- Visual feedback: dragged item lifts, gap appears at drop target\n- Drop saves the new order immediately\n- Uses [silent updates](item://c0c0c0c0-0010-0000-0000-000000000000) during drag for smooth interaction\n\n## See Also\n\n- [Spatial Windowing](item://ef793c27-2d4b-4c99-b05a-2769db5bc5a9) — The 2D alternative to linear lists\n- [Attachments](item://c0c0c0c0-0005-0000-0000-000000000000) — Ordered attachment arrays",
    "tags": [
      "a63eadd8-ec56-4163-acf2-207aa392069b"
    ],
    "hob": [
      [
        "let",
        {
          "v": [
